Kabul confirms Taliban capture Jalalabad city, blame Pakistan 
The Kabul government Wednesday admitted the Taliban religious militia
had taken the Afghan provincial capital of Jalalabad and accused
Pakistan of direct involvement.
Kabul faction spokesman Amrullah (Eds: one name), said the Taliban
attacked Jalalabad from two directions: via the southwest district of
Surkhrod and from Pakistan via the Torkham border post.
Kabul earlier claimed it had taken Jalalabad.
